    Create an agrisvy object

    createAgrisvy.Rd

    Create an agrisvy object

    createAgrisvy(
  svyName = "[Survey name]",
  author = "[Author]",
  language = "en",
  workingDir = NULL,
  path = NULL,
  type = NULL,
  varClassDir = "01_Variable classification",
  preProcScriptDir = "02_Pre-processing scripts",
  preprocDataDir = "03_Pre-processed data",
  anoScriptDir = "04_Anonymization report",
  anoDataDir = "04_Anonymization scripts",
  anoreportDir = "06_Anonymized data",
  fileDesDir = "07_Files description",
  infoLossReport = "08_Information loss report",
  tempfileDir = "09_Temporary_files",
  aobDir = "10_Miscellaneous"
)

    Arguments

    svyName

    name of the survey

    author

    author (institution)

    language

    language (display in predefined scripts)

    workingDir

    working directory (where the folders will be created)

    path

    path do the microdata of the survey

    type

    extension of the micro data example ".dta" for stata, ".sav" for SPSS

    varClassDir

    name of the variable classification folder

    preProcScriptDir

    name of the pre-processing scripts folder

    preprocDataDir

    name of the preprocessed data folder

    anoScriptDir

    name of the anonymization scripts folder

    anoDataDir

    name of the final anonymized data folder

    anoreportDir

    name of the anonymization report folder

    fileDesDir

    name of the file description folder

    infoLossReport

    name of the information loss report folder

    tempfileDir

    name of the temporary file folder

    aobDir

    name of the miscellenous folder

    Value

    a agrisvy object @importFrom methods new
